      <p>Additionally, since long non-coding RNAs (lncRNAs) may serve as marker genes (<xref rid="B15" ref-type="bibr">15</xref>), we compiled lncRNA databases for well-annotated plant species such as <italic toggle="yes">Arabidopsis thaliana</italic>, rice (<italic toggle="yes">Oryza sativa</italic>) and maize (<italic toggle="yes">Zea mays</italic>), from relevant studies (if available). For plant species with available lncRNA annotations, both lncRNAs and protein-coding genes were included for quantification analysis.</p>
